              <span id="reviewTextContainer2317449455" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18379451464114027500">This man was Pluto to the theatre universe. Despite what modern science says re Pluto’s status! He was in the same solar system but on a totally skewed orbit that was his own path, alone. I’ve been in “Fool for Love.” I’ve directed “Savage/Love.” I’ve seen (this year) “Action” and “Cowboy Mouth” as well as “True West” and “Curse of the Starving Class” back in the 80s. And I’ve read pretty much every script he published up to at least 1987. Every re-read/re-view is new. Never less than astonishin</span>
  <span id="freeText18379451464114027500" style="display:none">This man was Pluto to the theatre universe. Despite what modern science says re Pluto’s status! He was in the same solar system but on a totally skewed orbit that was his own path, alone. I’ve been in “Fool for Love.” I’ve directed “Savage/Love.” I’ve seen (this year) “Action” and “Cowboy Mouth” as well as “True West” and “Curse of the Starving Class” back in the 80s. And I’ve read pretty much every script he published up to at least 1987. Every re-read/re-view is new. Never less than astonishing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18379451464114027500" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


